ArrayList
=========

    --> Dynamic size
    --> Rich library functions

    --> An ArrayList should be created of non-primitive data types. Ex: Integer

            ArrayList<Integer> al = new ArrayList<Integer>(); or new ArrayList<Integer>(size);
            al.add(20);

    --> java.util package

    1) Adding elements:
       ---------------
            -- add() method
            -- add(element) : add an element to the end of an ArrayList
            -- add(int index, element) : adds an element at specific index in ArrayList

